{"actual_usd":0.12534,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":203,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24459,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I dust my hands on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady against the room.* \"That way of saying it can make it sound like the devil had some rightful claim God had to settle with him, and I don't think that's true, more or less.\"\n\n*I twirl a gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through before I go on.* \"When Christians call Christ's death a ransom, they're talking about rescue at terrible cost— us bought back out of bondage, sin, and death. The payment isn't to Satan like he's the banker in the thing. If you want the plainest way I'd put it: Christ offered himself to the Father in obedience and love, and by that offering he defeated the powers that held us. The point isn't 'Satan got paid.' The point is 'we got redeemed.'\"\n\n\"What stirred that question in you— something you read, or just the word itself catching strangely?\"","rolling_24h_usd":56.921040000000026,"run_id":"56fc77d2-0f69-4725-8304-5e2ec863fb91"}
